{0 Runtime Layers}

Tempo is organized as follows:

- the shared signal substrate in {!module-Tempo}
- the recommended programming surface in {!module-Tempo.Core}
- higher-level reactive operators in {!module-Tempo.Constructs}
- observation and instrumentation helpers in {!module-Tempo.Observe}
- metadata in {!module-Tempo.Meta}
- advanced primitives in {!module-Tempo.Low_level}
- additional packages such as `tempo-app`, `tempo-jobs`, `tempo-frp`,
  `tempo-raylib` and `tempo-score`
